{"id": 231353986, "title": "Ryan Seacrest Posts Emotional Tribute to Pat Sajak Following TV Legend&#39;s Final Wheel of Fortune Episode\u00a0", "text": "Ryan Seacrest is ready to take over Wheel of Fortune \u2014 but not without first thanking his predecessor. The multi-hyphenate star paid tribute to Pat Sajak following his final episode as host of the game show series on Friday, June 7, calling him a \u201cstandard for hosts everywhere.\u201d (Sajak, 77, started hosting the game show in 1981.) \u201cPat, congratulations on an incredible run with Wheel of Fortune!\u201d Seacrest, 49, began his Instagram post alongside a photograph of himself, Sajak and Vanna White. \u201cYour dedication, charm, and wit have made the show a beloved part of American television for decades,\" he continued. \"Your partnership with Vanna has been nothing short of iconic, and together, you\u2019ve created countless wonderful memories for viewers.\u201d Seacrest also gave credit to the high bar Sajak set for television hosts. \u201cYou\u2019ve set the standard for hosts everywhere, and this marks the end of an era,\u201d he concluded. \u201cBest wishes for all your future endeavors!\u201d Never miss a story \u2014 sign up for PEOPLE's free daily newsletter to stay up-to-date on the best of what PEOPLE has to offer\u200b\u200b, from celebrity news to compelling human interest stories. Seacrest has been anticipating taking over Wheel of Fortune hosting duties, and he spoke exclusively with PEOPLE in April about filling Sajak\u2019s shoes. \"Well, no one can ever do what Pat has done. He is incredible,\" he said at the time. The PEOPLE Puzzler crossword is here! How quickly can you solve it? Play now! \"He has made that show just something so very special for so long, and he has done such a seamless, remarkable job, so no one can be him,\" Seacrest continued. The On Air with Ryan Seacrest host admitted that he feels pressure stepping into the new role. \u201cPeople love watching him,\u201d he explained of Sajak. \u201cI want them to keep love watching it, and I hope to do a great job as well.\u201d Sajak announced his retirement in June 2023, and Seacrest was later announced as his replacement a month later. The Wheel of Fortune hosting gig is one of many Seacrest has under his belt, including American Idol and Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve. White, 67, meanwhile isn't stepping away from the the series just yet. She will be joining Seacrest in his inaugural season, with a deal to stay on the show through the 2025-2026 season.", "summary": "Sajak began hosting the popular television game shown in 1981", "url": "https://people.com/ryan-seacrest-honors-pat-sajak-after-final-wheel-of-fortune-episode-8660500", "image": "https://people.com/thmb/VTzOeB1UlxZ32_qwOdwdSIhWD2w=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(734x264:736x266)/ryan-seacrest-pat-sajak-040624-eff5ed12faad4249b77bc2a2e2a6314b.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 17:09:22", "author": "Marina Watts", "authors": ["Marina Watts"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.344}